==BigBlueButton==

URL = http://www.bigbluebutton.org/

"BigBlueButton is an open source web conferencing system built on over fourteen open source components to create an integrated solution that runs on mac, unix, or PC computers.

Following are some of the main features of BigBlueButton.

    * Desktop Sharing
    * Presentation
    * VOIP based Audio Conference
    * Video Conference
    * Public & Private Chat
    * Whiteboard & Annotation
    * Multilanguage support"


==Open Meeting==

URL = http://code.google.com/p/openmeetings/

"OpenMeetings is a free browser-based software that allows you to set up instantly a conference in the Web. You can use your microphone or webcam, share documents on a white board, share your screen or record meetings. It is available as hosted service or you download and install a package on your server with no limitations in usage or users.

    * Desktop Sharing
    * Presentation
    * VOIP based Audio Conference
    * Video Conference
    * Public & Private Chat
    * Whiteboard & Annotation
    * Recording (Complete Session and Interview styled)
    * Multilanguage support
    * Integration API and ready modules
    * LDAP-Connector"


